Date: 6 Jul 2000 06:27:19 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Reuters Online, Story Filed: Thursday, 6 Jul 2000 5:58 AM EST [edited

Snow Brand President Tetsuro Ishikawa said he would resign at the end of
September to take the blame for the food poisoning outbreak that has so far
left 12 027 people sick. Nearly 30 were still in hospital.
Most of the victims of Japan's worst such outbreak in 3 decades live in the
Osaka metropolitan area, in western Japan, and became ill with diarrhea and
vomiting after drinking the low-fat milk and other products from Snow
Brand's Osaka plant.
[Byline: Kazunori Takada
