[This thread is re-opened to report this large increase in numbers of cases
of staphylococcal food poisoning. I have extracted only 2 sentences from
the second report which covered much of the same ground as the first.
Apparently milk products not initially recalled have also been involved in
the poisonings. Now that the processing plant has been at least temporarily
shut down, and there has been more time to recall products and increase
public awareness, one can hope that the outbreak is over. - Mod.ES
